-- Dubai's DP World to price $1 bln convertible bond issue Thursday
-- By Archana Narayanan
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 02:27AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, June 12 (Reuters) - DP World <DPW.DI>, the Dubai-based ports operator, plans to raise a $1 billion convertible bond issue of ten years duration on Thursday to fund growth opportunities, a document from lead managers showed.

The bond is expected to pay a coupon in the range of 1.5 to 2 percent and will have a conversion premium between 35 and 40 percent, the document showed.